	(text "USB needs 90 Ohm differential traces. \nUsing JLCPCB's JLC04161H-7628 stackup.\nWhich with Signal Layer (Layer 1) and a GND layer (L2) below. And with 0.2mm tracks and separated 0.15mm gives a differential pair impedance of approximately 90 Ohms.\nFor USB1 will use a very short trace for D+ D- (around 2mm)\nFor USB2 (tracks that go to the internal ESP32 S3 pins and the pinout) the traces are long ~60mm for D+ D-, and have vias\nThe Development board from ESP32S3 has no problem with these differential pairs with vias and is a 2 board layer\nI also have to place vias because of the pinout of USB C and CP2102. Some other people have placed vias without problems for signal integrity"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 39.37 125.73 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 2 2)
			)
			(justify left bottom)
		)
		(uuid "e80d09b6-bd9d-4821-a298-15c60ea7c877")
	)
